WEBVTT

00:00:03.340 --> 00:00:04.640
and in fourth place is Excellency.

00:00:04.640 --> 00:00:06.410
They're now entering the final straight.

00:00:06.410 --> 00:00:08.980
On the inside, it's Tour d'Ivoire
hanging on at second place

00:00:08.980 --> 00:00:10.980
while Satono Diamond moves up on the outside!

00:00:10.980 --> 00:00:12.360
Go get 'em, Dia-chan!

00:00:15.800 --> 00:00:17.440
Satono Diamond on the outside!

00:00:17.440 --> 00:00:21.120
With 200 meters left, she's taken
the lead by one length!

00:00:21.120 --> 00:00:23.250
Satono Diamond presses through!

00:00:23.500 --> 00:00:24.820
And she crosses the goal!

00:00:24.820 --> 00:00:28.090
We've got a new heroine
in the Satono family!

00:00:25.250 --> 00:00:26.970
She did it!

00:00:26.970 --> 00:00:28.090
Way to run!

00:00:28.090 --> 00:00:32.090
Satono Diamond finishes her
debut race with a victory!

00:00:33.390 --> 00:00:36.010
I must say, that was impressive
acceleration from her.

00:00:36.010 --> 00:00:38.600
I'm looking forward to
seeing where her path goes.

00:00:39.280 --> 00:00:43.760
We've had a year of many
races featuring many stories,

00:00:43.760 --> 00:00:47.890
and next week the fan vote
for the Arima Kinen begins.

00:00:47.890 --> 00:00:51.850
Yamamoto-san, what kind of lineup
will we be looking at this year?

00:00:51.850 --> 00:00:54.150
Bravo Day won the Fall Tennoushou,

00:00:54.150 --> 00:00:57.740
and Kitasan Black won the Kikkashou,
so they seem very likely.

00:00:57.740 --> 00:01:01.110
But given that she's run in the
Arima Kinen three times before

00:01:01.110 --> 00:01:04.580
and is on a six-win streak in the G1,
I'd count on seeing Gold Ship.

00:01:05.000 --> 00:01:06.350
Where Gold Ship's concerned,

00:01:06.350 --> 00:01:10.120
I think that shocking Takarazuka Kinen
is still fresh in everyone's memories.

00:01:10.120 --> 00:01:13.370
That is true. I'd say that part of her
charm is you can never tell what'll happen

00:01:13.370 --> 00:01:14.840
when she's running in a race.

00:01:14.840 --> 00:01:19.060
I think we can look forward to seeing
how her fourth Arima Kinen turns out.

