00:01:36.360 --> 00:01:46.580
Umamusume

00:01:40.240 --> 00:01:46.580
Pretty Derby

00:02:51.040 --> 00:02:55.090
Episode 3
The Dream Never Ends

00:02:51.120 --> 00:02:55.900
All right, then, to Dia-chan's
debut and her first victory.

00:02:55.900 --> 00:02:57.370
Cheers!

00:02:57.370 --> 00:02:58.820
Cheers!

00:02:58.820 --> 00:03:03.410
S
A
T
O

00:02:58.820 --> 00:03:03.410
C
H
E
V
A
L

00:02:59.200 --> 00:03:01.680
How many times have we toasted already?

00:03:01.680 --> 00:03:03.410
Why am I even here?

00:03:03.410 --> 00:03:06.410
Faux Draft Beer

00:03:03.410 --> 00:03:06.410
Hey, you can never celebrate too much!

00:03:06.410 --> 00:03:09.670
Now, let's get a word from
today's star, Dia-chan herself!

00:03:11.740 --> 00:03:15.570
After making my debut today, I feel
like I'm finally at the starting line.

00:03:15.570 --> 00:03:18.140
Thank you all for cheering for me!

00:03:19.630 --> 00:03:22.060
Now, then! What would you say
is your goal moving forward?

00:03:22.060 --> 00:03:22.930
Goal?

00:03:22.930 --> 00:03:23.470
Yeah!

00:03:27.050 --> 00:03:30.230
I'm targeting next year's
classic Triple Crown races.

00:03:30.760 --> 00:03:32.220
First, at the Satsukishou,

00:03:32.220 --> 00:03:35.110
I want to win a G1 title that the
Satono family has wanted for so long.

00:03:37.480 --> 00:03:39.250
Let's work hard, Dia.

00:03:39.250 --> 00:03:41.070
And bring victory to the Satono family.

00:03:41.070 --> 00:03:42.320
Right!

00:03:42.570 --> 00:03:45.820
Next up, let's hear what
Cheval-chan's goal is!

00:03:45.820 --> 00:03:46.780
I have to do this?

00:03:46.780 --> 00:03:47.680
Sure do!

00:03:50.280 --> 00:03:51.540
I'm really frustrated that my injuries

00:03:51.970 --> 00:03:55.290
in the spring kept me from
running in the classics.

00:03:55.750 --> 00:03:59.050
So next year, I'm gonna turn
it around and win a G1!

00:04:00.010 --> 00:04:01.670
And now it's your turn.

00:04:01.670 --> 00:04:02.680
What, me?

00:04:02.680 --> 00:04:03.980
Go on, then.

00:04:03.980 --> 00:04:07.230
Uh, well, I guess...

00:04:07.820 --> 00:04:09.310
The Arima Kinen!

00:04:09.630 --> 00:04:12.690
I've always wanted to run
in the Arima Kinen!

00:04:13.460 --> 00:04:15.150
The Arima Kinen...

00:04:15.150 --> 00:04:17.150
You'll probably make it in, right?

00:04:17.150 --> 00:04:19.770
Yeah, considering you won the Kikkashou.

00:04:19.770 --> 00:04:22.170
Oh, right... maybe I will?

00:04:22.550 --> 00:04:23.900
That'd be great!

00:04:24.130 --> 00:04:26.050
I'm sure you'll make it.

00:04:26.050 --> 00:04:27.510
Dia-chan...

00:04:27.510 --> 00:04:28.420
Yeah!

00:04:28.420 --> 00:04:29.490
Okay!

00:04:29.490 --> 00:04:32.580
And now, a toast to all our futures!

00:04:32.580 --> 00:04:33.750
Again?!

00:04:34.250 --> 00:04:35.890
Yes!

00:04:35.890 --> 00:04:38.520
Then I get to run at Arima?!

00:04:38.520 --> 00:04:41.760
It's not final yet, but between
your schedule, the length,

00:04:41.760 --> 00:04:45.150
and how you ran at the Kikkashou,
I think you've got a proper chance.

00:04:45.150 --> 00:04:46.510
That's great!

00:04:46.510 --> 00:04:48.750
Last time, you were racing against
other girls from your generation,

00:04:48.750 --> 00:04:53.210
but at Arima, you'll be going up against
fully formed runners from the senior class.

00:04:53.570 --> 00:04:54.700
You better be ready!

00:04:54.700 --> 00:04:55.570
Right!

00:04:57.020 --> 00:04:58.640
Congratulations, Kita-san.

00:04:58.640 --> 00:04:59.520
This is great!

00:04:59.520 --> 00:05:00.520
You've made it it!

00:05:00.830 --> 00:05:02.230
Good luck, Kita-chan!

00:05:02.610 --> 00:05:04.960
Teio-san, everyone...

00:05:05.560 --> 00:05:07.380
Right! I'll do my best!

00:05:09.080 --> 00:05:10.200
Wh-What was that!?

00:05:11.080 --> 00:05:13.240
Oof, what a mess.

00:05:13.240 --> 00:05:14.460
It really is.

00:05:14.460 --> 00:05:16.050
Hey! What the hell did you do?!

00:05:16.050 --> 00:05:18.040
I had some trouble getting out of the gate.

00:05:18.040 --> 00:05:19.840
Aw, come on, I'm begging you...

00:05:19.840 --> 00:05:22.860
I don't need to deal with another
nightmare like at the Takarazuka Kinen.

00:05:22.860 --> 00:05:24.190
You messed that one up.

00:05:24.190 --> 00:05:25.470
Really bad, in fact.

00:05:25.470 --> 00:05:28.830
You finally managed to
pass the gate exam again,

00:05:28.830 --> 00:05:30.740
but if you screw up at the Japan Cup...

00:05:30.740 --> 00:05:31.970
Relax.

00:05:31.970 --> 00:05:35.390
I'm gonna have a perfect start next
time and get my seventh G1 turf win.

00:05:35.390 --> 00:05:38.550
From there, it's into the Arima
for a historic eight-win streak!

00:05:38.550 --> 00:05:42.230
Dream a little less and train a little more!

00:05:42.230 --> 00:05:44.190
I cannot believe her at times.

00:05:44.190 --> 00:05:46.540
Golshi-san seems really fired up.

00:05:46.540 --> 00:05:48.860
Well, I'm expecting a lot
from you too, Kitasan!

00:05:49.500 --> 00:05:52.250
Okay! I'm fired up too!

00:05:52.740 --> 00:05:56.250
Arima, Arima, Arima!

00:05:56.570 --> 00:06:00.000
Aim for the Arima!

00:06:00.000 --> 00:06:03.410
Okay, no matter who I race
against, I won't lose!

00:06:00.000 --> 00:06:04.760
Team Spica

00:06:00.000 --> 00:06:04.760
Join us or get
left in the mud

00:06:04.760 --> 00:06:09.510
I heard your melody during the
chrysanthemum concerto, my dear!

00:06:09.980 --> 00:06:12.820
Belissima, Kitasan Black.

00:06:12.700 --> 00:06:15.390
S
O
U

00:06:12.820 --> 00:06:15.390
I am Sounds of Earth.

00:06:15.390 --> 00:06:17.020
O-Okay.

00:06:18.540 --> 00:06:21.520
A race is an ensemble performance
between the earth and a horse girl!

00:06:21.800 --> 00:06:25.240
And all horse girls are gifted musicistas!

00:06:25.940 --> 00:06:29.930
Now, you and I will make
such beautiful music...

00:06:29.930 --> 00:06:31.760
Your face! Your face is really close!

00:06:31.760 --> 00:06:32.930
When I fly against you,

00:06:32.930 --> 00:06:35.530
I will demonstrate my
virtuoso talent at Arima...

00:06:35.530 --> 00:06:37.120
Way too close!

00:06:37.820 --> 00:06:39.370
Enough, Earth!

00:06:42.170 --> 00:06:44.250
What the heck are you doing?

00:06:44.250 --> 00:06:45.530
Nature-san!

00:06:45.530 --> 00:06:48.850
Oh my, and just when we were harmonizing.

00:06:49.220 --> 00:06:52.010
I'm looking forward to it, Kitasan Black.

00:06:52.010 --> 00:06:54.590
When we join the orchestra
at the Arima Kinen!

00:06:55.320 --> 00:06:56.600
That girl...

00:06:56.600 --> 00:07:00.490
Sorry about that, Kitasan. I guess
our newbie was being kind of a pain.

00:07:01.660 --> 00:07:02.670
Your newbie?!

00:07:05.610 --> 00:07:08.710
So, Earth-san's on Team Canopus.

00:07:08.710 --> 00:07:10.940
She's a bit of an oddball.

00:07:11.750 --> 00:07:14.120
But there's more to her than that.

00:07:14.120 --> 00:07:15.810
Earth is strong.

00:07:15.810 --> 00:07:19.550
Her running in the Arima might mean
the first G1 victory ever for Canopus!

00:07:20.120 --> 00:07:22.280
You're gonna be running in it too, right?

00:07:23.020 --> 00:07:28.130
Yeah. It's not finalized yet,
but my trainer says it's pretty likely!

00:07:28.130 --> 00:07:29.450
You sound thrilled.

00:07:29.450 --> 00:07:31.880
Yeah! I've always wanted to run in it!

00:07:32.740 --> 00:07:37.230
The Arima Kinen is a special race to me.

00:07:34.280 --> 00:07:36.140
Arima Kinen

00:07:38.410 --> 00:07:39.890
That race, huh?

00:07:40.370 --> 00:07:42.700
You've run in it before
too, right, Nature-san?

00:07:42.700 --> 00:07:45.480
And somehow I got third
place three years in a row.

00:07:45.740 --> 00:07:48.740
But the Arima Kinen is
a bit of a special one.

00:07:48.740 --> 00:07:50.040
It really is!

00:07:50.860 --> 00:07:53.040
Thank you so much, Nature-san.

00:07:53.040 --> 00:07:54.740
Wh-Where'd that come from?

00:07:54.740 --> 00:07:59.240
I'm only able to run in the Arima
because I won the Kikkashou.

00:07:59.240 --> 00:08:03.070
If you hadn't given me all that advice...

00:08:03.070 --> 00:08:05.610
You did all the running yourself.

00:08:05.610 --> 00:08:07.780
I didn't really do anything.

00:08:07.780 --> 00:08:08.990
Still...

00:08:08.990 --> 00:08:12.880
Don't worry about that.
Just focus on running in the Arima.

00:08:13.280 --> 00:08:16.010
If you need to talk, I'll be here.

00:08:17.010 --> 00:08:20.010
Right! Thank you so much, Nature-sensei!

00:08:20.610 --> 00:08:23.160
C-Come on, "sensei"?

00:08:28.670 --> 00:08:31.640
Hell yeah! How's that?!
Was that a perfect start or what?!

00:08:31.640 --> 00:08:33.740
Yeah. If you can keep it up,
you should be fine.

00:08:33.740 --> 00:08:37.000
How you like me now?! I've got the
Japan Cup wrapped up at this rate!

00:08:37.000 --> 00:08:40.230
Honestly... you must realize
that complacency is a threat.

00:08:40.230 --> 00:08:41.580
Hey, thanks, McQueen.

00:08:46.530 --> 00:08:47.920
Almost done!

00:08:47.920 --> 00:08:49.250
Hang in there, Kita-san!

00:08:55.800 --> 00:08:58.300
You managed to put in your best
time today at the very end there!

00:08:58.300 --> 00:08:59.760
Yes!

00:08:59.760 --> 00:09:01.130
Here you go.

00:09:01.130 --> 00:09:02.680
Thank you!

00:09:03.150 --> 00:09:05.370
Hey, you just finish up too?

00:09:05.370 --> 00:09:06.270
Yeah!

00:09:06.270 --> 00:09:08.330
But I'm gonna do one more lap!

00:09:09.360 --> 00:09:10.700
Kita-san, your bottle!

00:09:13.270 --> 00:09:15.130
She's still running?

00:09:15.130 --> 00:09:17.130
She's hit her growth spurt, after all.

00:09:24.410 --> 00:09:27.330
There's only a month left in the year.

00:09:27.540 --> 00:09:30.590
Have you all decided what
you want for Christmas?

00:09:30.810 --> 00:09:31.960
There!

00:09:31.960 --> 00:09:33.870
You're a life-saver, Kita-chan!

00:09:33.870 --> 00:09:35.340
It was no trouble at all!

00:09:35.660 --> 00:09:38.890
That reminds me. I voted for you
to get into the Arima Kinen.

00:09:38.890 --> 00:09:40.410
R-Really?!

00:09:40.410 --> 00:09:45.000
Me too. Here, take this.
We're rooting for you, so work hard.

00:09:45.600 --> 00:09:47.350
Thank you so much!

00:09:47.350 --> 00:09:49.350
The Japan Cup Turns into War!
Gold Ship Comes In at 10th Place after Failing to Come from Behind!!

00:09:49.350 --> 00:09:51.360
Gold Ship Comes In at 10th Place after Failing to Come from Behind!!

00:10:12.880 --> 00:10:14.630
Come on, Kita-chan, wake up.

00:10:16.880 --> 00:10:18.960
I miss my bed...

00:10:18.960 --> 00:10:23.140
Breakfast this morning is your favorite:
carrots and rice, with banana steak.

00:10:23.140 --> 00:10:27.250
Okay then! I'm gonna
eat a lot and train a lot again today!

00:10:27.580 --> 00:10:29.130
What's going on?

00:10:32.650 --> 00:10:34.650
BREAKING NEWS

00:10:32.650 --> 00:10:34.650
GOLD SHIP
URGENT PRESS CONFERENCE

00:10:32.650 --> 00:10:34.650
BEWARE OF FLASHING CAMERA LIGHTS

00:10:35.380 --> 00:10:36.540
Golshi-san?

00:10:37.090 --> 00:10:39.910
I appreciate you all showing up today.

00:10:39.910 --> 00:10:44.790
BREAKING NEWS

00:10:39.910 --> 00:10:44.790
GOLD SHIP
URGENT PRESS CONFERENCE

00:10:39.910 --> 00:10:44.790
BEWARE OF FLASHING CAMERA LIGHTS

00:10:40.120 --> 00:10:43.540
I've called this conference in
order to make an announcement

00:10:43.540 --> 00:10:44.790
regarding a decision I've made.

00:10:45.130 --> 00:10:46.350
What decision?

00:10:46.350 --> 00:10:48.650
My name is Gold Ship,

00:10:47.040 --> 00:10:52.790
BREAKING NEWS

00:10:47.040 --> 00:10:52.790
GOLD SHIP
URGENT PRESS CONFERENCE

00:10:47.040 --> 00:10:52.790
BEWARE OF FLASHING CAMERA LIGHTS

00:10:48.650 --> 00:10:52.790
and after the Arima Kinen, I will be
moving on to the Dream Trophy League.

00:10:56.160 --> 00:11:00.300
That would mean you won't be running
in the Twinkle Series anymore.

00:11:00.560 --> 00:11:01.750
That's right.

00:11:02.320 --> 00:11:04.550
As far as my Twinkle Series goes...

00:11:04.860 --> 00:11:07.180
The Arima Kinen will be my last run.

00:11:13.980 --> 00:11:17.980
Umamusume

00:11:13.980 --> 00:11:17.980
Pretty Derby

00:11:14.570 --> 00:11:16.410
Her last run?

00:11:28.780 --> 00:11:29.850
Golshi-san!

00:11:30.830 --> 00:11:34.580
Um... Is it true? About your last run.

00:11:35.140 --> 00:11:35.770
Yep.

00:11:37.770 --> 00:11:39.840
The Satsukishou and Kikkashou.

00:11:40.140 --> 00:11:43.900
My first Arima Kinen too.
I managed to clobber everyone.

00:11:45.540 --> 00:11:48.640
I started in the back, and just flew up...

00:11:48.640 --> 00:11:49.930
Leaving them all in the dust.

00:11:50.830 --> 00:11:53.620
That was how I used to race.

00:11:56.090 --> 00:11:56.820
But lately...

00:11:58.960 --> 00:12:01.640
At some point, I couldn't do it anymore.

00:12:03.150 --> 00:12:05.910
I started having trouble
controlling my emotions...

00:12:05.910 --> 00:12:08.100
You weren't like that before?

00:12:08.100 --> 00:12:10.510
Got bad at exiting the gate too.

00:12:10.510 --> 00:12:12.710
It's like I've lost all kinds of focus.

00:12:12.710 --> 00:12:13.710
What the hell do I discard here?

00:12:13.710 --> 00:12:15.610
Hasn't that always been the case?

00:12:17.780 --> 00:12:19.670
Anyway, that about covers it.

00:12:19.670 --> 00:12:22.600
And... that's why you're
having your last run?

00:12:22.600 --> 00:12:24.590
Quit looking like someone died.

00:12:24.590 --> 00:12:27.350
My dream's not over yet.

00:12:27.740 --> 00:12:30.220
At the Arima before last,
I lost to the tyrant,

00:12:30.220 --> 00:12:32.850
and in the next one,
the lady stole it from me.

00:12:33.060 --> 00:12:36.460
When I take the Arima this year,
it'll be seven G1 wins for me...

00:12:36.460 --> 00:12:38.230
I'll savor the sweet taste of victory.

00:12:38.460 --> 00:12:39.830
Golshi-san...

00:12:42.410 --> 00:12:45.360
You're gonna cry for my last run?

00:12:45.360 --> 00:12:46.360
Because...

00:12:47.000 --> 00:12:52.480
Your last run... I might win it
and ruin your taste of victory!

00:12:52.480 --> 00:12:55.290
Why you little—where do you get off?!

00:12:59.340 --> 00:13:02.050
Say your prayers, you little runt!

00:13:02.050 --> 00:13:05.760
And you had better not pull any punches
on my last run, growth spurter!

00:13:06.340 --> 00:13:09.810
Don't be late out of the gate, Golshi-san!

00:13:11.810 --> 00:13:16.430
Why, is this the mouth that's
spouting off such cheeky nonsense?!

00:13:18.650 --> 00:13:21.360
Now then! Let's celebrate
Dia-chan's second victory...

00:13:21.360 --> 00:13:23.360
Cheers!

00:13:23.360 --> 00:13:25.360
Celebrating Dia-chan's second win!

00:13:26.750 --> 00:13:30.510
I hope my win today helps
you tomorrow, Kita-chan.

00:13:30.510 --> 00:13:34.370
It totally will! I'm feeling
really brave and motivated!

00:13:34.370 --> 00:13:36.120
(Turf)

00:13:34.370 --> 00:13:36.120
Arima Kinen

00:13:34.370 --> 00:13:36.120
December 27th
Sunday

00:13:34.370 --> 00:13:36.120
Nakayama Racecourse

00:13:34.760 --> 00:13:36.120
It's almost time.

00:13:36.120 --> 00:13:38.760
Yeah... for the Arima Kinen.

00:13:41.180 --> 00:13:42.200
Kita-chan?

00:13:43.150 --> 00:13:46.490
A last run... I wonder what that feels like.

00:13:51.660 --> 00:13:52.830
I don't know...

00:13:53.520 --> 00:13:56.750
But I don't think we need to know, just yet.

00:13:59.030 --> 00:14:03.780
All we can do is focus
on the races in front of us.

00:14:04.740 --> 00:14:05.940
Dia-chan...

00:14:06.830 --> 00:14:10.090
You're going to send Golshi-san off,
right? Then good luck!

00:14:10.090 --> 00:14:10.770
Yeah!

00:14:11.150 --> 00:14:12.730
I'm gonna win it!

00:14:14.330 --> 00:14:18.280
There's a chill in the winter air
here at the Nakayama Racecourse

00:14:18.280 --> 00:14:21.290
with a crowd of 120,000 gathered this year.

00:14:21.290 --> 00:14:25.580
But the expectations of these fans
is enough to fight through the frosty weather.

00:14:25.580 --> 00:14:29.790
It all comes down to this:
the G1 Arima Kinen!

00:14:29.790 --> 00:14:32.170
With me is Yamamoto-san on color,

00:14:32.170 --> 00:14:34.410
and I have to say, we've got
quite an impressive lineup.

00:14:34.410 --> 00:14:35.430
That is true.

00:14:35.430 --> 00:14:38.810
Coming off two G1 wins and and second place
in the fan vote, we've got Bravo Day,

00:14:39.070 --> 00:14:41.900
and the winner of this year's
Kikkashou, Kitasan Black,

00:14:41.900 --> 00:14:44.900
along with Sounds of Earth, who has been
looking sharper and sharper since fall.

00:14:44.900 --> 00:14:48.220
The sibling clash between River Light
and Parole should also be interesting.

00:14:48.220 --> 00:14:51.470
But I have to say, the spotlight
is on the number one in the fan vote,

00:14:51.470 --> 00:14:55.450
who will be running her last run
in the Twinkle Series, Gold Ship.

00:14:55.450 --> 00:14:57.450
Come on, Gold Ship!

00:14:57.450 --> 00:14:59.210
You can do it, Earth!

00:14:59.210 --> 00:15:01.170
Go, Earth!

00:15:03.420 --> 00:15:07.400
It's cold, but hot, and I'm
nervous, but really excited.

00:15:07.400 --> 00:15:09.170
This is the Arima Kinen.

00:15:11.350 --> 00:15:15.200
I'm... standing on the stage for the Arima.

00:15:19.430 --> 00:15:25.440
Arima Kinen
Nakayama               Turf\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h

00:15:38.950 --> 00:15:42.210
And the horse girls have entered the gate.

00:15:42.210 --> 00:15:43.960
This will be the grand prix
that closes the year,

00:15:43.960 --> 00:15:44.960
the Arima Kinen.

00:15:46.490 --> 00:15:49.210
And they're off to a beautiful start!

00:15:51.470 --> 00:15:53.070
Okay!

00:15:53.070 --> 00:15:54.430
She's got a bit of a competition,

00:15:54.430 --> 00:15:56.180
but Kitasan Black has taken the lead.

00:15:56.180 --> 00:16:00.680
On the inside is All Haiyu, and behind
her is Sounds of Earth!

00:16:00.680 --> 00:16:03.770
Gold Ship is at the rear, as is her style.

00:16:03.770 --> 00:16:07.730
And the 16 runners are now entering
the home stretch of their first lap!

00:16:09.260 --> 00:16:12.200
Go for it, Earth! Win a G1!

00:16:12.200 --> 00:16:15.040
Who am I supposed to
root for, Golshi or Kitasan?!

00:16:15.040 --> 00:16:16.830
Both of them, obviously!

00:16:20.170 --> 00:16:21.910
You can do it, Kita-chan!

00:16:24.040 --> 00:16:24.990
So this is Gold Ship's—

00:16:24.990 --> 00:16:27.340
So this is Gold Ship's last run.

00:16:27.340 --> 00:16:28.690
Everyone dreams about a grand prix win,

00:16:28.690 --> 00:16:32.300
and countless famous stories have
played out here at the Arima Kinen.

00:16:32.300 --> 00:16:34.880
Symboli Rudolf proved she was
the strongest of her generation.

00:16:34.880 --> 00:16:37.210
Manhattan Cafe marked a
changing of the guard.

00:16:37.210 --> 00:16:37.680
Who are you?

00:16:37.680 --> 00:16:40.040
And then, in her last run
for the Twinkle series,

00:16:40.040 --> 00:16:42.050
Oguri Cap made an
explosive return to form.

00:16:42.050 --> 00:16:42.680
Seriously, who?!

00:16:42.680 --> 00:16:44.520
With their similar hair color,

00:16:44.520 --> 00:16:48.350
it's hard not to hope for something
similar from Gold Ship...

00:16:48.990 --> 00:16:49.940
Care for a drink?

00:16:49.940 --> 00:16:52.190
Kitasan Black has control
of the momentum for now.

00:16:52.190 --> 00:16:54.700
With the cheers pushing her forward,
she's passed the first corner!

00:16:54.700 --> 00:16:56.570
Next up is #12, Parole.

00:16:56.570 --> 00:16:58.320
Then on the inside, All Haiyu,

00:16:58.320 --> 00:17:01.110
and Sounds of the Earth
running along the outside,

00:17:01.110 --> 00:17:06.670
along with #4, Bravo Day, #5,
Great House, and #2, Brave Target!

00:17:06.670 --> 00:17:09.130
I can feel the pressure
coming from the veterans!

00:17:09.370 --> 00:17:12.180
Rounding the second corner, they're
headed down the other straightaway.

00:17:12.180 --> 00:17:14.370
We've got a narrow, lengthy lineup this time.

00:17:14.370 --> 00:17:19.600
Still at the head is #11, Kitasan Black,
with #12, Parole, behind her.

00:17:24.130 --> 00:17:25.560
And now we see a blurry gray silhouette

00:17:24.480 --> 00:17:25.560
There she goes!

00:17:25.560 --> 00:17:27.310
as Gold Ship takes action!

00:17:30.630 --> 00:17:34.400
She's charging steadily on! We can see
her gaining steadily on the outside!

00:17:34.400 --> 00:17:35.040
Can—

00:17:35.040 --> 00:17:36.400
Can Gold Ship pull it off?

00:17:36.400 --> 00:17:38.030
With such a long spurt?!

00:17:41.030 --> 00:17:44.660
Coming around the fourth corner, we have
River Light and then Sounds of Earth!

00:17:44.660 --> 00:17:47.090
On the inside, All Haiyu
is picking up the pace!

00:17:45.650 --> 00:17:47.670
All right, go for it, Earth!

00:17:47.950 --> 00:17:49.880
They've entered the final straight!

00:17:49.880 --> 00:17:52.670
Kitasan Black is in the lead! Kitasan Black!

00:17:52.670 --> 00:17:54.170
You can do it, Kita-chan!

00:17:54.170 --> 00:17:56.340
Two hundred meters to go! Hang in there!

00:17:56.340 --> 00:17:57.260
Come on!

00:17:57.260 --> 00:18:00.880
Kitasan Black is on the run!
River Light is moving up!

00:18:03.390 --> 00:18:07.850
But here comes Gold Ship!
Gold Ship is closing in!

00:18:09.940 --> 00:18:11.910
It's the return of Gold Ship!

00:18:11.910 --> 00:18:14.400
Show us an amazing come-from-behind win again!

00:18:14.400 --> 00:18:16.000
Go, Gold Ship!

00:18:16.000 --> 00:18:17.680
Come on, you can do it!

00:18:17.680 --> 00:18:19.700
Use everything you've got!

00:18:19.700 --> 00:18:22.700
The unsinkable Gold Ship's last run!

00:18:22.700 --> 00:18:27.160
Will the glittering cheers of
the crowd lead her to victory?!

00:18:33.430 --> 00:18:37.130
But she's not gaining!
Gold Ship is not gaining!

00:18:44.390 --> 00:18:48.890
In the front is Kitasan Black,
River Light, and #7, All Haiyu!

00:18:48.890 --> 00:18:50.430
Kitasan Black holds on!

00:18:50.430 --> 00:18:52.330
Almost there... almost there!

00:18:52.330 --> 00:18:54.150
Almost there! Almost there!

00:18:56.110 --> 00:18:59.290
But here comes All Haiyu, with the pass!

00:18:59.290 --> 00:19:01.570
And Sounds of Earth moves up as well!

00:19:01.800 --> 00:19:03.580
All Haiyu places first!

00:19:03.810 --> 00:19:04.830
And there's the goal!

00:19:05.370 --> 00:19:08.700
All Haiyu has won on this
most glamorous of stages!

00:19:08.700 --> 00:19:10.080
I did it!

00:19:10.080 --> 00:19:12.660
In second place is Sounds of Earth!

00:19:11.730 --> 00:19:14.710
Ah, never a finer concerto have I ever heard!

00:19:15.080 --> 00:19:17.210
Second place! You did good!

00:19:17.210 --> 00:19:20.340
The Kikkashou winner,
Kitasan Black, is third place.

00:19:20.340 --> 00:19:24.530
And the most popular runner, Gold Ship,
finishes her last run in eighth.

00:19:39.030 --> 00:19:40.400
What's up?

00:19:40.400 --> 00:19:43.660
I thought you were gonna win on my last run?

00:19:44.130 --> 00:19:45.380
Golshi-san...

00:19:46.690 --> 00:19:48.160
Golshi-san!

00:19:52.440 --> 00:19:53.710
Golshi-san!

00:19:56.090 --> 00:19:58.840
Seriously, quit acting like someone died.

00:20:08.890 --> 00:20:10.160
You did great!

00:20:10.160 --> 00:20:11.230
Good race!

00:20:11.230 --> 00:20:14.170
Thank you for keeping us on the
edge of our seats yet again!

00:20:14.170 --> 00:20:17.970
Six G1 wins! That's an
amazing record, Gold Ship!

00:20:17.970 --> 00:20:19.530
And it ain't over yet!

00:20:23.140 --> 00:20:26.320
Say your prayers, Orfevre and Gentildonna!

00:20:27.230 --> 00:20:31.830
Payback for the Twinkle Series is coming
for you in the Dream Trophy League!

00:20:31.830 --> 00:20:36.330
My dream will never end! And I'm
gonna prove that to all of you!

00:20:37.120 --> 00:20:39.110
We're going to see them battle again...

00:20:40.110 --> 00:20:42.420
The golden voyage isn't finished yet!

00:20:44.430 --> 00:20:59.920
Golshi! Golshi!

00:20:59.920 --> 00:21:15.540
Golshi! Golshi!

00:21:00.410 --> 00:21:04.220
Honestly... she's standing out more
in eighth place than the winner.

00:21:04.220 --> 00:21:06.910
That's our Gold Ship, all right.

00:21:16.090 --> 00:21:19.540
And now a toast to my first Arima!

00:21:19.540 --> 00:21:22.550
Faux Draft Beer

00:21:22.550 --> 00:21:24.450
You were so close, Kita-chan.

00:21:24.450 --> 00:21:26.680
A third place finish at the Arima
is something to be proud of.

00:21:26.680 --> 00:21:28.660
Yeah, that was a good race.

00:21:28.660 --> 00:21:30.200
Thanks, everybody!

00:21:31.530 --> 00:21:32.520
But...

00:21:34.120 --> 00:21:37.060
I wish I could've won the Arima Kinen.

00:21:37.930 --> 00:21:39.120
Kita-chan...

00:21:40.260 --> 00:21:41.320
Hey.

00:21:42.890 --> 00:21:44.130
Golshi-san?

00:21:45.000 --> 00:21:45.610
Yours now.

00:21:48.030 --> 00:21:49.490
You've got one so far.

00:21:51.400 --> 00:21:53.300
I managed six...

00:21:53.300 --> 00:21:55.460
So let's see how many you can put together.

00:21:57.790 --> 00:21:59.060
Does she mean...

00:22:06.220 --> 00:22:08.970
I'm gonna surpass you, Golshi-san!

00:22:08.970 --> 00:22:11.350
I'll get six, and even more!

00:22:13.590 --> 00:22:15.930
My dream has just begun.

00:22:16.430 --> 00:22:19.200
And when the New Year begins, I'm sure...

00:22:19.750 --> 00:22:23.320
Okay! Here's a toast to my future!

00:22:23.320 --> 00:22:24.550
Another one?!

